<paragraph id="8BB136F1FFCF9412B38D9A2EFD42F98F" blockId="37.[151,716,1609,1635]" box="[151,716,1609,1635]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">
<heading id="D0F9819DFFCF9412B38D9A2EFD42F98F" bold="true" box="[151,716,1609,1635]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D72FFCF9412B38D9A2EFD42F98F" authority="Palisot de Beauvois" box="[151,716,1609,1635]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Polistes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major" subGenus="Palisotius">
<emphasis id="B97AEAE3FFCF9412B38D9A2EFD42F98F" bold="true" box="[151,716,1609,1635]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis id="B97AEAE3FFCF9412B38D9A2EFF7AF98F" bold="true" box="[151,244,1609,1635]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Polistes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B97AEAE3FFCF9412B21E9A2EFEF4F98F" bold="true" box="[260,378,1609,1635]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Palisotius</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B97AEAE3FFCF9412B2969A2EFE5AF98F" bold="true" box="[396,468,1609,1635]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">major</emphasis>
Palisot de Beauvois
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136F1FFCF9411B38D9AE8FEE1FEF1" blockId="37.[151,1436,1679,2029]" lastBlockId="38.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="339" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis id="B97AEAE3FFCF9412B38D9AE8FE1BF944" bold="true" box="[151,405,1679,1704]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">
Paramere (
<figureCitation id="13352A74FFCF9412B2019AE8FE08F944" box="[283,390,1679,1704]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[250,1392,1265,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[194,1393,1258,1910]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 40. Male genitalia of Polistes (Palisotius) major—A= paramere, lateral view; B= aedeagus, ventral view; C= aedeagus, lateral view; D= digitus, lateral view; E= cuspis, lateral view. Scale bar = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606418/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Fig. 40A</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
(1) about three times longer than wide at the middle; (2) lateral groove very shallow, almost straight; (3) parameral spine long (about 1/6 the total length of paramere), pointed apically and inclined slightly to the side with very long and dense bristles; (4) paramere lobe widely developed and rounded; (5) inferior portion of paramere narrow, about half the width at the middle portion. 
<emphasis id="B97AEAE3FFCF9412B04E9A9BFBF8F8F9" bold="true" box="[852,1142,1788,1813]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13352A74FFCF9412B0C29A9BFBE8F8F9" box="[984,1126,1788,1813]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[250,1392,1265,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[194,1393,1258,1910]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 40. Male genitalia of Polistes (Palisotius) major—A= paramere, lateral view; B= aedeagus, ventral view; C= aedeagus, lateral view; D= digitus, lateral view; E= cuspis, lateral view. Scale bar = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606418/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Fig. 40B, C</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
robust; (1) apical portion with intermediate and serrated denticulation, extended on the apical portion to the end of median expansion, lateral margin straight; (2) penis valve weakly dilated and with a slight central entrance, with a weakly bilobed appearance (little more than 1/3 of the total length of apical portion); (3) median expansion widely developed, pointed apex; (4) lateral apodeme directed forward and almost the same size than ventral process, (5) ventral process rounded and dilated; (6) inferior portion of aedeagus curved, in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B97AEAE3FFCF9412B0659BD7FBEDF825" bold="true" box="[895,1123,1968,1993]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">
Digitus (
<figureCitation id="13352A74FFCF9412B0FD9BD7FBDBF825" box="[999,1109,1968,1993]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[250,1392,1265,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[194,1393,1258,1910]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 40. Male genitalia of Polistes (Palisotius) major—A= paramere, lateral view; B= aedeagus, ventral view; C= aedeagus, lateral view; D= digitus, lateral view; E= cuspis, lateral view. Scale bar = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606418/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Fig. 40D</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
slender; (1) apical process developed, about twice longer than the digitus base, same width from the base to the apex, (2) apex pointed; (3) anteroventral lobe short and rounded apically; (4) punctation strong and forming a central band around the base of the digitus; (5) evanescent bristles. 
<emphasis id="B97AEAE3FFCC9411B1329CDBFC8FFF39" bold="true" box="[552,769,188,213]" pageId="38" pageNumber="339">
Cuspis (
<figureCitation id="13352A74FFCC9411B1929CDBFD7CFF39" box="[648,754,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1932,1954]" captionTargetBox="[250,1392,1265,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[194,1393,1258,1910]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 40. Male genitalia of Polistes (Palisotius) major—A= paramere, lateral view; B= aedeagus, ventral view; C= aedeagus, lateral view; D= digitus, lateral view; E= cuspis, lateral view. Scale bar = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606418/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="339">Fig. 40E</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
slender; (1) apex pointed and tapering abruptly to the end; (2) short and dense bristles, but more on lateral margin; (3) punctation restricted on the lateral lobe; (4) lower part of cuspis damaged.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C314657AFFCC9411B3DD9D40FDE1FE40" pageId="38" pageNumber="339" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB136F1FFCC9411B3DD9D40FDE1FE40" blockId="38.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="38" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis id="B97AEAE3FFCC9411B3DD9D40FEB5FEAC" bold="true" box="[199,315,295,320]" pageId="38" pageNumber="339">Remarks.</emphasis>
In 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B00FFCC9411B2789D40FD02FEAC" author="Richards, O. W." box="[354,652,295,320]" pageId="38" pageNumber="339" refId="ref24573" refString="Richards, O. W. (1978) The social wasps of the Americas (excluding the Uespinae). British Museum of Natural History, London, 580 pp." type="book" year="1978">Richards (1978: 445–448)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D72FFCC9411B1829D4EFD79FED3" box="[664,759,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Polistes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="339" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis id="B97AEAE3FFCC9411B1829D4EFD79FED3" box="[664,759,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="339">P. major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was divided into eight subspecies. Such division was based on color variation, which is not considered in this work. The male was described for 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D72FFCC9411B74F9D2AFB73FE88" authority="major" box="[1109,1277,333,356]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Polistes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="339" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="major" subSpecies="major">
<emphasis id="B97AEAE3FFCC9411B74F9D2AFB73FE88" box="[1109,1277,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="339">P. major major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the male genitalia in pp. 445–446. His description complements ours in relation to the teeth of the aedeagus- about in 20 number. Other structures match with ours.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
